1
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,466
welcome back

2
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:04,666
today we are going to move on to the UEV tier

3
00:00:04,766 --> 00:00:06,700
after making the intro quest

4
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:10,633
we have to decide on which branch we want to make our first progress

5
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:15,666
and getting the last Circuit assembler out of the way didn't unlock any further path

6
00:00:15,666 --> 00:00:17,466
that's because to make use of it

7
00:00:17,466 --> 00:00:20,166
we also need the motors of the new tier

8
00:00:20,166 --> 00:00:23,766
but those require a material that isn't found in our galaxy

9
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,166
to adventure that far

10
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:27,000
we are going to need a mother ship

11
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:27,500
however

12
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,233
to build one

13
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:30,233
we have to first make a shuttle

14
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:33,500
which is crafted with something called radox polymer

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,266
which is an endgame plastic

16
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:39,366
which requires us to build the last chemical chain of this series

17
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:39,833
however

18
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,900
the starting point is something called xenoxene

19
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:47,000
which is produced by the most delicate bacteria there is

20
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,666
xenoxene xenoxsis

21
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:49,500
however

22
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:52,833
this is not even a bacteria we can find in nature

23
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:58,633
we have to do a lot of weird DNA messing around in our biolab to obtain that species

24
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:03,766
it all starts from taking some excrement bacteria out of a rotten spider eye

25
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,766
once we isolated it

26
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:07,300
we take it into a vat

27
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,566
where we will be making lots of biohazardous fluid

28
00:01:10,766 --> 00:01:12,400
by working that stuff

29
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:17,366
we can extract all sorts of useful ingredients that we are going to need soon

30
00:01:17,966 --> 00:01:18,200
then

31
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,600
we start working on the basic bacteria for xenoxene

32
00:01:21,666 --> 00:01:23,766
Barnardfis arboriatoris

33
00:01:23,766 --> 00:01:26,500
which can be picked out of some barnarda logs

34
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,900
the next step is to try to extract its DNA

35
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,466
and this is a low success chance

36
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:35,600
only 1 out of 20 samples succeeded

37
00:01:36,233 --> 00:01:38,433
now we want to analyze this sample

38
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,200
and save it on a data orb

39
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,233
however the process is delicate

40
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:45,000
and it often fails at saving the correct data

41
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:48,966
so after stocking up a lot of stuff to do more tries

42
00:01:48,966 --> 00:01:52,566
we managed to get a bunch of DNA samples to try again

43
00:01:52,766 --> 00:01:54,266
this time luckily

44
00:01:54,266 --> 00:01:57,766
we got the data analyzed correctly at the first try

45
00:01:58,566 --> 00:02:01,100
now we use that and the data from another bacteria

46
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,833
to create the plasmid for the new bacteria we want to create

47
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:06,700
once we get it

48
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:11,366
we use it to mutate the TCetiEis bacteria into xenoxene xenoxsis

49
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:14,766
which we shall take to a new set of vats

50
00:02:14,766 --> 00:02:17,633
where we will finally be preparing xenoxene

51
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:19,800
the basis for radox production

52
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:21,633
once we have that

53
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:25,700
it's just a matter of a processing chain of less than a dozen machines

54
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,200
to get the radox polymer

55
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,033
with that

56
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:32,033
we can now craft the lightweight plates required for the shuttle

57
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:35,166
meanwhile we also make its schematics

58
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,833
and the parts for our upcoming mother ship

59
00:02:38,066 --> 00:02:39,733
once everything is ready

60
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:41,566
we build our new spaceship

61
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,266
however for now

62
00:02:43,266 --> 00:02:45,633
more than a spaceship it is a satellite

63
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:47,700
since it has no engines

64
00:02:47,866 --> 00:02:50,666
so we quickly order a thruster for our ship

65
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:52,700
once the new engine is in place

66
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,900
and filled with naquadah fuel

67
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,400
we can move our ship

68
00:02:56,866 --> 00:03:01,400
but it appears that this engine is not strong enough to move us to a new galaxy

69
00:03:01,566 --> 00:03:04,566
we could increase its size or add a second one

70
00:03:04,566 --> 00:03:07,633
but we are instead going to upgrade to an ion thruster

71
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:10,800
which can reach 10 times higher speeds

72
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,800
with the new engine equipped

73
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,300
we can now move our mother ship to the Ra solar system

74
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,366
and thanks to the ion thrusters

75
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,800
this will only take 13 minutes

76
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,200
once we reach destination

77
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,466
we quickly move to the main belt

78
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,300
which was the actual destination that made us build the whole mother ship

79
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,033
this is not a planet

80
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:36,300
but a belt of asteroids orbiting the RA star

81
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:38,666
our mother ship is too big

82
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:41,700
and can't risk getting damaged by the asteroids

83
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:44,266
so we get closer by using the shuttle

84
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,600
and then we start wandering around

85
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,400
until we find what we came here for

86
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,000
tengam

87
00:03:51,966 --> 00:03:54,866
once we found an asteroid made out of the ore

88
00:03:54,866 --> 00:03:56,633
we have to face some guards

89
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,266
and then the mining operation can start

90
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:03,966
we are going to hide from the swarms of robots inside the asteroid

91
00:04:03,966 --> 00:04:06,366
where we will be setting up a void miner

92
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,433
and this miner is going to mine the void literally

93
00:04:11,066 --> 00:04:12,266
once we get back

94
00:04:12,266 --> 00:04:15,166
after extracting the raw tengam from its ore

95
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:19,033
we proceed into refining it with an electromagnetic separator

96
00:04:19,466 --> 00:04:23,433
and the first usage we have for the new material is an electromagnet

97
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:26,066
to speed up its refinement process

98
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,433
and then we can finally craft the new motors

99
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:33,466
the first UEV thing we want to make is a space pump

100
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:36,266
however that highlighted a bottleneck

101
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,866
we are too slow at compressing infinity

102
00:04:39,266 --> 00:04:40,033
luckily

103
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:43,200
there is now an upgrade to the neutronium compressor

104
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,233
however to craft it

105
00:04:45,233 --> 00:04:51,066
we need super dense plates which must be made with a hot isostatic pressurization unit

106
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:56,000
which is a machine which has to be toggled on and off to avoid overheating

107
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,366
so here we have it built

108
00:04:58,366 --> 00:05:01,433
with a sensor that will stop it when it heats too much

109
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:04,633
so we better use this only when required

110
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,300
to avoid extra clogging

111
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:10,266
and thus we have our new neutronium compressor

112
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:14,833
which is going to be way faster at compressing Infinity Catalyst

113
00:05:15,866 --> 00:05:19,066
and thus we can have our new space pumping station

114
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:22,566
the first gas we will want to pump is hydrogen

115
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:26,066
however that tank could be small

116
00:05:26,066 --> 00:05:27,866
so we go back to our compressor

117
00:05:27,866 --> 00:05:30,633
to craft something that can carry more fluid

118
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:32,800
a digital singularity cell

119
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:37,800
that thing will allow us to store all the hydrogen we could possibly need

120
00:05:37,966 --> 00:05:40,966
we already passed the tank by 100 times

121
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:43,633
but the cell is still almost empty

122
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:47,066
moving on to get the new circuits

123
00:05:47,066 --> 00:05:50,233
after photonically enriching an americium doped wafer

124
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:53,866
we find out we need some more purified water to cut it

125
00:05:54,366 --> 00:05:56,300
so we go back to our water line

126
00:05:56,300 --> 00:06:00,766
and add more steps after the extreme temperature fluctuation plant

127
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:04,800
namely the high energy laser purification unit

128
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,766
which will pass the water under lasers of all the colors

129
00:06:07,766 --> 00:06:13,166
to make sure it hits any possible thing that could have survived the 1000 Kelvin temperature

130
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:17,800
and then the residual decontaminant degasser purification unit

131
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,633
which has some complex logic

132
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:22,100
and will require us to decode its signals

133
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,400
and act accordingly

134
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,233
and since we are not experienced enough with Redstone

135
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:30,800
we just brute force it with Steve's factory manager

136
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,700
and with this purified water

137
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:37,166
we can now cut our optically perfected wafers

138
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:38,500
next

139
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:43,666
we add some nanites to our wafers with the help of a strong laser and some plasma

140
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:48,966
and we smash everything with some extra purified water in our sledge hammer

141
00:06:48,966 --> 00:06:51,300
to expose some circuit material

142
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:55,333
we bring that materials to our space elevator

143
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,966
where with the help of some space assemblers

144
00:06:57,966 --> 00:07:00,500
we upload the raw materials above the clouds

145
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,500
for some operations that require a zero gravity ambient

146
00:07:04,666 --> 00:07:07,266
then we download the so assembled RAM

147
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:08,466
next

148
00:07:08,466 --> 00:07:10,666
we start preparing a new factory area

149
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:13,700
for the stuff we will build with all that space RAM

150
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:18,433
then we make one floor for the basic optical processor

151
00:07:19,066 --> 00:07:21,066
one for the optical assembly

152
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,000
one for the computer

153
00:07:23,466 --> 00:07:25,900
and finally one for the main frame

154
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,400
now that we have this new circuit

155
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,100
we shall put it to good use

156
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,966
and the first machine we can build with our new circuits is

157
00:07:32,966 --> 00:07:36,366
the dimensionally transcendent plasma forge

158
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:39,566
that machine is going to require a lot of materials

159
00:07:39,566 --> 00:07:42,500
not to mention the amount of blocks for the structure

160
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:46,366
we will probably want to make it out of the new Infinity coils

161
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:48,400
which other than Infinity

162
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,900
will now also require circuits

163
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:54,700
and it is now time to put our AE2 system to test again

164
00:07:54,866 --> 00:07:58,200
crafting just the controller is going to take some time

165
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,900
so in the meanwhile

166
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:03,066
we can prepare the other stuff that is going to be needed

167
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:07,666
the plasma Forge uses a fuel dimensionally transcendent catalysts

168
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:11,033
which are made by mixing together many different plasmas

169
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,433
since we do not have a plasma mixer

170
00:08:13,433 --> 00:08:18,233
we shall make those as a multi step process with our normal industrial mixers

171
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:23,033
and that is going to be a really slow and power intensive process

172
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:25,400
even with our 12 socketed machines

173
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:28,266
and after mixing the raw plasmas

174
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,766
we give a finishing touch with our new laser

175
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,833
going back to our DTPF crafting

176
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:36,866
after taking note of one of the weirdest bottlenecks

177
00:08:36,866 --> 00:08:40,900
we notice that our 6 general purpose assembly line aren't enough

178
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:42,866
so we added some more

179
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,033
and we needed a second data bank

180
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:48,100
to share all of the data sticks from the old one

181
00:08:48,566 --> 00:08:51,466
and all of those rainbow spaghetti reminded us that

182
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:54,600
we must also add one more colored laser to our battery

183
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,766
to bring power to the location where we are going to build the new machine

184
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,500
which in the meantime

185
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:03,233
we have completed in all of it majesty

186
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:10,300
this block is going to greatly reduce the amount of resources we need to process some of the endgame materials

187
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:13,866
or drastically cut the crafting time of working others

188
00:09:14,066 --> 00:09:15,833
but what we want right now

189
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:18,100
is completely new and weird stuff

190
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,500
such as tesseracts

191
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,866
however before getting into crafting those

192
00:09:22,866 --> 00:09:25,433
there is some stuff we have to worry about

193
00:09:25,566 --> 00:09:29,533
the main cost of running this structure is in the catalysts used as fuel

194
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:34,466
we can cut the cost by half by never letting this machine shut down

195
00:09:35,066 --> 00:09:37,033
so once we start it

196
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:40,900
we will have a system to keep it running on slower stuff perpetually

197
00:09:41,466 --> 00:09:42,000
to do so

198
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:48,966
we simply start throwing in stuff to work whenever the crafting input bus for on demand craftings empties

199
00:09:48,966 --> 00:09:51,300
and as you can see

200
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:54,800
we are slowly building up a discount in fuel usage

201
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,400
but we can do better

202
00:09:56,633 --> 00:10:00,700
the thing we are passively doing while no crafts are queued is hypogen

203
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,666
hypogen is a really useful material

204
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:05,200
which for example

205
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:08,100
can cut the recurrence of crafting batteries

206
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,700
or help us make better fuels for our generators

207
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:16,100
but the main issue is that to make hypogen we are using hypogen

208
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,700
there is a better recipe with higher yield

209
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,566
and no hypogen usage

210
00:10:20,566 --> 00:10:23,100
but that requires hypogen coils

211
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:29,500
the issue is that we are making 19 litres per second when our DTPF would otherwise be idling

212
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,433
to make new coils we need two millions of it

213
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,500
that's around 40 hours

214
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:39,000
the other way we have for making hypogen is with fusion

215
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,200
but that requires dragon blood

216
00:10:41,966 --> 00:10:45,700
we had obtained some of that stuff when we slew the Ender Dragon

217
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,400
but that won't be enough

218
00:10:47,566 --> 00:10:51,766
since we are also going to need a lot of that stuff in a couple of tiers

219
00:10:51,766 --> 00:10:53,866
we shall look for a better source

220
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,766
but that's a story for the next episode

221
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:59,033
but before greeting

222
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,800
we shall find a morale for this episode

223
00:11:01,966 --> 00:11:03,633
and I think here the lesson is that

224
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:06,900
the real lesson was within us all of the time

225
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,433
bye bye

226
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,466
欢迎回来！

227
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:04,666
今天我们要进入UEV电压

228
00:00:04,766 --> 00:00:06,700
完成序章后

229
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:10,633
我们必须决定先发展哪个分支

230
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:15,666
做出最后一个电路装配机并没有解锁其他任务

231
00:00:15,666 --> 00:00:17,466
那是因为想利用它

232
00:00:17,466 --> 00:00:20,166
我们还需要UEV马达

233
00:00:20,166 --> 00:00:23,766
但这需要一种我们星系没有的物质

234
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,166
想去那么远的地方

235
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:27,000
母舰必不可少

236
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:27,500
然而

237
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,233
想做一个

238
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:30,233
我们得先做个穿梭机

239
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:33,500
它需要拉多X聚合物

240
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,266
这是后期的一种塑料

241
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:39,366
需要我们建造这个系列的最后一个化学链

242
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:39,833
然而

243
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,900
它的起点是一种叫做异氙的东西

244
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:47,000
它是由最脆弱的细菌产生的

245
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,666
异氙菌

246
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:49,500
然而

247
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:52,833
自然界甚至找不到这种细菌

248
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,333
为了得到它

249
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:58,633
我们不得不在实验室混合各种DNA

250
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:03,766
先是从腐烂蜘蛛眼中提取粪便细菌

251
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,766
一旦分离出大肠杆菌

252
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:07,300
我们把它放进培养缸里

253
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,566
我们将制造大量生物危害液体

254
00:01:10,766 --> 00:01:12,400
通过处理那些东西

255
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:17,366
我们可以获得各种马上要用到的原料

256
00:01:17,966 --> 00:01:18,200
然后

257
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,600
我们开始研究异氙的前置细菌

258
00:01:21,666 --> 00:01:23,766
巴纳德菌

259
00:01:23,766 --> 00:01:26,500
它们可以从巴纳德树木中挑选出来

260
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,900
下一步是尝试提取它的DNA

261
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,466
成功机率很低

262
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:35,600
20个样本中只会成功1个

263
00:01:36,233 --> 00:01:38,433
现在我们分析这个样本

264
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,200
并将其保存在数据球上

265
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,233
然而，这个过程不确定性很高

266
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:45,000
它经常无法保存正确的数据

267
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:48,966
所以在储备了很多东西来做更多的尝试之后

268
00:01:48,966 --> 00:01:52,566
我们得到了一堆DNA样本来重试

269
00:01:52,766 --> 00:01:54,266
这次，幸运的是

270
00:01:54,266 --> 00:01:57,766
我们一发入魂

271
00:01:58,566 --> 00:02:01,100
现在我们用它和另一种细菌的数据

272
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,833
来创造异氙菌所需的质粒

273
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:06,700
一旦我们得到它

274
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:11,366
我们用它把鲸鱼座T星E菌变异为异氙菌

275
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:14,766
然后将它带到一套新的培养缸里

276
00:02:14,766 --> 00:02:17,633
我们将在那里制备异氙

277
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:19,800
用作拉多X产线的基础

278
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:21,633
一旦我们有了那个

279
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:25,700
只需要堆不到十二个机器

280
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,200
便能轻松获得拉多X聚合物

281
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,033
有了那个

282
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:32,033
我们现在可以制作母舰所需的轻质合金板

283
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:35,166
同时我们还制作了它的设计图

284
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,833
还有即将到来的母舰的零件

285
00:02:38,066 --> 00:02:39,733
一旦一切准备就绪

286
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:41,566
直接建造母舰

287
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,266
然而目前

288
00:02:43,266 --> 00:02:45,633
它更像一个卫星

289
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:47,700
因为它没有引擎

290
00:02:47,866 --> 00:02:50,666
所以很快为我们的船订购了一个推进器

291
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:52,700
一旦新引擎就位

292
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,900
并装满硅岩燃料

293
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,400
飞船便可以动起来了

294
00:02:56,866 --> 00:03:01,400
但是这个引擎似乎还不足以把我们带到一个新的星系

295
00:03:01,566 --> 00:03:04,566
我们可以增加它的尺寸或添加第二个

296
00:03:04,566 --> 00:03:07,633
但我们要升级到离子推进器

297
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:10,800
这可以达到10倍以上的速度

298
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,800
配备完新的引擎

299
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,300
我们现在可以把母舰移到Ra星系了

300
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,366
多亏了离子推进器

301
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,800
这只需要13分钟

302
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,200
一旦我们到达目的地

303
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,466
我们快速移动到主轨道

304
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,300
这就是我们建造整艘母舰的真正目的地

305
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,033
这不是行星

306
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:36,300
而是围绕RA星的小行星带

307
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:38,666
我们的母舰太大了

308
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:41,700
不能冒被小行星击中的险

309
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:44,266
所以我们用穿梭机靠近

310
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,600
我们在四处逛逛

311
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,400
直到找到目标

312
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,000
生磁

313
00:03:51,966 --> 00:03:54,866
一旦我们发现了一颗由矿石构成的小行星

314
00:03:54,866 --> 00:03:56,633
解决掉一些守卫

315
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,266
然后采矿作业就可以开始了

316
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:03,966
我们要躲避小行星内部成群的机器人

317
00:04:03,966 --> 00:04:06,366
在那里设置一个虚空矿厂

318
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,933
就和字面上的一样

319
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:10,433
它将挖掘虚空

320
00:04:11,066 --> 00:04:12,266
一旦我们回去

321
00:04:12,266 --> 00:04:15,166
从矿石中提炼出生磁后

322
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:19,033
我们继续用电磁离析器精炼它

323
00:04:19,466 --> 00:04:23,433
这种新材料的第一个用途是电磁铁

324
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:26,066
用来加快精炼速度

325
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,433
然后我们就可以制作新的电动马达

326
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:33,466
我们的第一个UEV装置是太空钻机

327
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:36,266
然而，这展露了一个瓶颈

328
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,866
无尽催化剂压缩得太慢了

329
00:04:39,266 --> 00:04:40,033
幸运地

330
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:43,200
我们可以升级中子压缩机

331
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,233
然而要制作它

332
00:04:45,233 --> 00:04:51,066
我们需要用热等静压装置制造的超致密板

333
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:56,000
这是一台必须反复开关以避免过热的机器

334
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,366
所以我们起了一台

335
00:04:58,366 --> 00:04:59,700
带有一个传感器

336
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,433
当它过热时会停止它

337
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:04,633
所以我们最好只在需要时使用它

338
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,300
以避免额外的堵塞

339
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:10,266
由于我们有了新的中子压缩机

340
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:14,833
压缩无尽催化剂的速度快得多了

341
00:05:15,866 --> 00:05:19,066
这样我们就有了新的太空钻机

342
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:22,566
我们要抽的第一种气体是氢气

343
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:26,066
然而，这个量子缸可能显得很小

344
00:05:26,066 --> 00:05:27,866
所以回到我们的压缩机

345
00:05:27,866 --> 00:05:30,633
制造能携带更多液体的东西

346
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:32,800
数字奇点单元

347
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:37,800
它可以储存我们需要的所有氢气

348
00:05:37,966 --> 00:05:40,966
我们已经存超过量子缸100倍容量了

349
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:43,633
但元件还是几乎是空的

350
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:47,066
继续制作新电路

351
00:05:47,066 --> 00:05:50,233
在光子富集掺杂镅的晶圆之后

352
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:53,866
我们发现需要更纯净的水才能切割

353
00:05:54,366 --> 00:05:56,300
所以我们回到净化水线

354
00:05:56,300 --> 00:06:00,766
并在五级水厂后添加更多步骤

355
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:04,800
即高能激光净化装置

356
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,766
它将用各种颜色的激光照射水

357
00:06:07,766 --> 00:06:13,166
以确保它击中任何可能在1000K温度幸存下来的东西

358
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:17,800
然后是残留去污剂脱气器净化装置

359
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,633
它有一些复杂的逻辑

360
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:22,100
并要求我们解码它的信号

361
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,400
并采取相应行动

362
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,233
既然我们对红石不太熟练

363
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:30,800
所以使用SFM与它硬碰硬

364
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,700
有了这种纯净水

365
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:37,166
我们现在可以切割光学性质完美的晶圆

366
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:38,500
接下来

367
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:41,600
我们在强激光和等离子体的帮助下

368
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,666
向晶圆中添加纳米蜂群

369
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:48,966
在锻造锤内配合净化水砸碎一切

370
00:06:48,966 --> 00:06:51,300
来暴露出一些电路材料

371
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:55,333
我们把那些材料带到太空电梯

372
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,966
在一些太空组装机的帮助下

373
00:06:57,966 --> 00:07:00,500
我们将原材料上云

374
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,500
做低重力环境下的处理

375
00:07:04,666 --> 00:07:07,266
然后再下载如此装配的内存

376
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:08,466
接下来

377
00:07:08,466 --> 00:07:10,666
我们准备一个新的厂区

378
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:13,700
量产使用了太空内存的光学电路系列

379
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:18,433
我们为基本的光学处理器做一层

380
00:07:19,066 --> 00:07:21,066
光学处理器集群一层

381
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,000
光学处理器超级电脑一层

382
00:07:23,466 --> 00:07:25,900
最后，光学处理器主机一层

383
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,400
现在我们有了新电路

384
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,100
我们将好好利用它

385
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,966
我们用新电路制造的第一台机器是

386
00:07:32,966 --> 00:07:36,366
超维度等离子锻炉

387
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:39,566
那台机器需要很多材料

388
00:07:39,566 --> 00:07:42,500
更不用说众多的结构方块了

389
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:46,366
我们想做无尽等级的DTPF

390
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:48,400
现在无尽线圈除了无尽

391
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,900
还需要电路板来制造

392
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:54,700
现在是时候再次压力测试AE了

393
00:07:54,866 --> 00:07:58,200
光是制作控制器就需要一些时间

394
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,900
所以与此同时

395
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:03,066
我们可以准备其他需要的东西

396
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:07,666
DTPF使用的超维度燃料

397
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:11,033
它们是由许多不同的等离子体混合制成的

398
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,433
因为我们没有等离子搅拌机

399
00:08:13,433 --> 00:08:18,233
我们将使用搅拌机来分步完成

400
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:23,033
这将是一个非常缓慢和耗能的过程

401
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:25,400
12个能源仓的机器都跟不上

402
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:28,266
混合原始等离子体后

403
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,766
我们用新的激光刻蚀机做最后润色

404
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,833
回到DTPF制作

405
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:36,866
在注意到奇怪的瓶颈之后

406
00:08:36,866 --> 00:08:40,900
我们发现6条通用装配线是不够的

407
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:42,866
所以我们又加了一些

408
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,033
我们需要第二个数据库

409
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:48,100
来共享旧数据库的所有数据

410
00:08:48,566 --> 00:08:51,466
那些混乱的激光管道提醒我们

411
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:54,600
我们必须再添加一条激光管道

412
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,766
给我们要建造新机器的地方供电

413
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,500
与此同时

414
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:03,233
我们已经完成奇观的建设

415
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:07,266
这个多方块结构将大幅度减少

416
00:09:07,266 --> 00:09:10,300
制造后期材料所需的原料

417
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:13,866
也可以大幅度减少一些材料的制作时间

418
00:09:14,066 --> 00:09:15,833
但是我们现在想要的

419
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:18,100
是全新的奇怪东西

420
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,500
比如粗制超立方体

421
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,866
然而，在制作这些之前

422
00:09:22,866 --> 00:09:25,433
有些事我们得担心

423
00:09:25,566 --> 00:09:29,533
运行DTPF的主要成本在于催化剂燃料

424
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:34,466
我们可以通过不关闭这台机器来减少一半的成本

425
00:09:35,066 --> 00:09:37,033
所以一旦开始

426
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:40,900
我们将保持其在低耗材的情况下一直运行

427
00:09:41,466 --> 00:09:42,000
为此

428
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,333
只要主动制作的输入总线清空

429
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:48,966
我们便加入维持机器运行的原料

430
00:09:48,966 --> 00:09:51,300
如你所见

431
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:54,800
燃料损耗正在慢慢下降

432
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,400
但我们可以做得更好

433
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,433
当没有材料排队时

434
00:09:58,433 --> 00:10:00,700
将被动生产的是海珀珍

435
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,666
海珀珍是一种非常有用的材料

436
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:05,200
例如

437
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:08,100
可以截断电池的套娃

438
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,700
或者给发电机制造更好的燃料

439
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:16,100
但问题是，海珀珍的合成套娃了

440
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,700
有一个更高产的配方

441
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,566
并且不使用海珀珍

442
00:10:20,566 --> 00:10:23,100
但那需要海珀珍线圈

443
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:25,933
问题是，在DTPF待机时

444
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:29,500
我们将被动生产19L/s的海珀珍

445
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,433
而我们需要2ML

446
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,500
大约40小时

447
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:39,000
另一种制造海珀珍的方法是核聚变

448
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,200
但那需要龙血

449
00:10:41,966 --> 00:10:45,700
我们在杀死末影龙时得到了一些

450
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,400
但这还不够

451
00:10:47,566 --> 00:10:51,766
我们在其他电压也会需要很多龙血

452
00:10:51,766 --> 00:10:53,866
我们应该寻找它更好的来源

453
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,766
但这是下一集的故事

454
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:59,033
但在Welcome back之前

455
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,800
我们要鼓起士气

456
00:11:01,966 --> 00:11:03,633
我认为今天的教训是

457
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:06,900
真正的教训一直在我们心中

458
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,433
拜拜

459
00:07:32,966 --> 00:07:36,366
（之后用英文缩写DTPF指代）

